{"cursor":"7045","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n{| border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 style=\"width:250px; float:right;\nclear:right; border: 1px #aaaaaa solid; border-collapse: collapse;\"\n|- align=\"center\" style=\"font-size: 110%; padding: 5px; background-color:\n|#ccccff;\" | 'Lists of monarchs of medieval Spain:' - style=\"font-size: 90%;\n|padding: 0 5px 0 5px;\" |List of '''Aragonese''' monarchs - style=\"font-size:\n|90%; padding: 0 5px 0 5px;\" |List of '''Asturian''' monarchs - style=\"font-\n|size: 90%; padding: 0 5px 0 5px;\" |List of '''Castilian''' monarchs - style=\"font-\n|size: 90%; padding: 0 5px 0 5px;\" |List of monarchs of '''al-Andalus''' - style=\"font-\n|size: 90%; padding: 0 5px 0 5px;\" |List of '''Galician''' monarchs - style=\"font-\n|size: 90%; padding: 0 5px 0 5px;\" |List of monarchs of '''Granada''' - style=\"font-\n|size: 90%; padding: 0 5px 0 5px;\" |List of '''Leonese''' monarchs - style=\"font-\n|size: 90%; padding: 0 5px 0 5px;\" |'List of monarchs of'Majorca'' - style=\"font-\n|size: 90%; padding: 0 5px 0 5px;\" |List of '''Navarrese''' monarchs - style=\"font-\n|size: 90%; padding: 0 5px 0 5px;\" |List of '''Valencian''' monarchs - style=\"font-\n|size: 90%; padding: 0 5px 0 5px;\" |List of '''Visigothic''' monarchs - style=\"font-\n|size: 90%; padding: 0 5px 0 5px;\" |List of Galician '''Suebic''' monarchs - }\n\n\nThe Kingdom of Majorca (1231â1344) was created by James I of Aragon following\nhis conquest in 1229 and the subsequent surrender of sovereignty by the Muslim\nrulers in of the Balearic Islands in 1231. It was ruled in conjunction with the\nCrown of Aragon until his death when by will it passed to a younger son, James\n(II), who ruled the kingdom as nominal vassal of the Aragonese Crown. He was\nremoved by his nephew Alfonso III of Aragon, who conquered the island of Majorca\nin 1285 and Ibiza in 1286, and effectively recovered Minorca from Moorish rule.\nBy the Treaty of Anagni of 1295, however, these island territories were yielded\nback to James. In 1344, the kingdom was again united with the Crown of Aragon\nbut still disputed by pretenders until 1403. It subsequently formed an\nadministrative kingdom within the Crown of Spain periodically included in the\nroyal style as in Philip II's in the 1584 Treaty of Joinville until the Nueva\nPlanta Decrees abolished these divisions in 1714.\n","linknr":225,"url":"List_of_monarchs_of_Majorca","recorded":1375079214,"links":["/w/index.php?title=List_of_monarchs_of_Majorca&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=List_of_monarchs_of_Majorca&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","#mw-navigation","#p-search","/wiki/File:Escudo_de_Espa%C3%B1a_(mazonado).svg","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/85/Escudo_de_Espa%C3%B1a_%28mazonado%29.svg/50px-Escudo_de_Espa%C3%B1a_%28mazonado%29.svg.png","/wiki/List_of_Aragonese_monarchs","/wiki/List_of_Asturian_monarchs","/wiki/List_of_Castilian_monarchs","/wiki/List_of_Umayyad_governors_of_al-Andalus","/wiki/List_of_Galician_monarchs","/wiki/Nasrid_dynasty","/wiki/List_of_Leonese_monarchs","/wiki/List_of_Navarrese_monarchs","/wiki/List_of_Valencian_monarchs","/wiki/Kings_of_the_Visigoths#Kings_of_the_Visigoths","/wiki/Suebic_Kingdom_